Algorithms
 
Algorithms define the logical processes that power key system features. They ensure that bookings, authentication, and inventory checks operate reliably and consistently. Each algorithm below is presented using clear pseudocode, followed by an explanation of how it supports the system’s functionality and prevents common operational issues identified in the proposal.
 
Seat Allocation Algorithm

 
Code
START
User selects event
Load seat map for selected event
User clicks on a seat
IF seat.status == "available" THEN
   Temporarily reserve seat
   Add seat to user's basket
ELSE
   Display "Seat Unavailable"
END IF
 
Explanation: This algorithm prevents doublebooking by checking the realtime status of each seat before allowing a user to reserve it. Once selected, the seat is temporarily locked until the user completes or cancels the purchase, ensuring accuracy during busy event periods.
 
Equipment Availability Algorithm

 
Code
START
User selects rehearsal room and time slot
User selects equipment items
FOR each item in selected equipment
   CHECK availability for the chosen time slot
   IF item.quantity_available < 1 THEN
       Display "Equipment Unavailable"
       STOP booking process
   END IF
END FOR
Proceed to confirm booking
 
Explanation: This algorithm ensures that equipment cannot be overbooked. It checks availability for the exact time slot selected by the musician. If any item is unavailable, the system stops the booking and alerts the user, preventing scheduling conflicts and inventory errors.
 
User Login Authentication Algorithm

 
Code
START
User enters email and password
Hash the entered password
Retrieve stored user record by email
IF no record found THEN
   Display "Invalid Credentials"
ELSE IF hashed_password == stored_password_hash THEN
   Grant access based on user.role
ELSE
   Display "Invalid Credentials"
END IF
 
Explanation: This algorithm ensures secure login for all user groups. Passwords are compared using hashing rather than plain text, protecting user data. Rolebased access ensures that public users, musicians, staff, and management only access the features intended for them.
 
Rehearsal Room Conflict Check Algorithm

 
Code
START
User selects room, date, and time slot
Retrieve all existing bookings for that room
FOR each booking in room_bookings
   IF selected_time overlaps with booking.time THEN
       Display "Time Slot Unavailable"
       STOP booking process
   END IF
END FOR
Allow user to continue booking
 
Explanation: This algorithm prevents doublebooking of rehearsal rooms by checking for overlapping time slots. It ensures that musicians cannot accidentally book a room already reserved by someone else.
 
Ticket Purchase Confirmation Algorithm

 
Code
START
User proceeds to checkout
Verify all selected seats are still reserved
IF any seat.status != "reserved" THEN
   Display "Seat No Longer Available"
   Return user to seat selection
ELSE
   Mark seats as "sold"
   Generate booking record
   Display confirmation
END IF
 
Explanation: This final verification step ensures that no two users can purchase the same seat during hightraffic periods. It confirms seat availability before completing the transaction and generating the ticket record.
 
 
 
